&quot;Adaptive Dual-Scale Denoising,&quot;</em><span> which introduces a no=
vel approach in diffusion models. While the paper wasn&#8217;t flawless, it=
 proposed an innovative direction and showed good empirical results from ex=
periments it conducted and reviewed. In addition, The AI Scientist has gene=
rated legit papers in other machine learning fields like language modeling =
and transformers.</span></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: =
16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">It doesn&#8217;t take an AI r=
esearcher to see how a recursive AI Scientist could meaningfully accelerate=
 the pace of discovery in both AI and other scientific fields. Unlike human=
 scientists, an AI Scientist could run against hundreds of research directi=
ons at once, incorporate all experimental data across its projections, feed=
 that data back into new brainstorm seshes, work 24/7, and do all of it at =
the fraction of the cost of a human scientist. It&#8217;s not super hard to=
 imagine a world in which an AI Scientist is just pumping out breakthrough =
after breakthrough.</p><p style=3D"color: rgb(54, 55, 55); font-size: 16px;=
 line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>This is the world that Leopo=
ld Aschenbrenner described in </span><em><a href=3D"https://substack.com/re=
